.TH MAPS-MAVLINK-TLOG-TAIL 1 "23 July 2026" "maps-apps 1.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
maps-mavlink-tlog-tail \- extract the final duration from a MAVLink TLOG
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B maps-mavlink-tlog-tail
.I input.tlog output.tlog duration
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B maps-mavlink-tlog-tail
scans a timestamped MAVLink TLOG and writes only records from its final requested duration. Original timestamps and MAVLink packet bytes are copied unchanged.
.PP
The command does not rewrite system IDs, recalculate checksums, or alter packet contents.
.SH ARGUMENTS
.TP
.I input.tlog
Input TLOG file.
.TP
.I output.tlog
Output TLOG file. It must differ from the input file.
.TP
.I duration
Tail duration. Accepted forms are seconds, MM:SS, HH:MM:SS, or an integer followed by ms, s, m, or h.
.SH EXAMPLES
Extract the final 40 minutes:
.PP
.EX
maps-mavlink-tlog-tail original.tlog final-40-minutes.tlog 40:00
.EE
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /opt/maps/apps/mavlink_tools.jar
MAVLink tools JAR installed by the maps-apps package.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR maps-mavlink-tlog-system-id (1),
.BR maps-mavlink-replay (1),
.BR maps-mavlink-inspect (1),
.BR maps-apps (7)
.SH AUTHOR
MapsMessaging B.V.
